{
  "book_code": "T4-NF-01",
  "title": "How We Cook Jollof Rice",
  "strand": "Tafiya",
  "level": "Level 4",
  "tafiya_name": "Tafiya",
  "type": "Nonfiction",
  "theme": "",
  "cover": {
    "image": "books/T4-NF-01/images/T4-NF-01_FC.png",
    "layout": "cover_standard",
    "logo_mode": "locked_brand_zones"
  },
  "pages": [
    {
      "page": 1,
      "image": "books/T4-NF-01/images/T4-NF-01_P1.png",
      "text": "Jollof rice is one of Nigeria's most loved foods. It is cooked at celebrations and eaten every day in many homes.",
      "layout": "image_top_text_bottom",
      "text_band": "medium",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "page": 2,
      "image": "books/T4-NF-01/images/T4-NF-01_P2.png",
      "text": "To make jollof, you need rice, tomatoes, peppers, onions, palm oil, and seasoning. These are the things that go into a good pot of jollof.",
      "layout": "image_top_text_bottom",
      "text_band": "medium",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "page": 3,
      "image": "books/T4-NF-01/images/T4-NF-01_P3.png",
      "text": "First, blend the tomatoes, peppers, and onions together until they are smooth. This is the tomato base.",
      "layout": "image_top_text_bottom",
      "text_band": "short",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "page": 4,
      "image": "books/T4-NF-01/images/T4-NF-01_P4.png",
      "text": "Next, heat the palm oil in a big pot. Add the tomato base and fry it, stirring, until the raw smell is gone.",
      "layout": "image_top_text_bottom",
      "text_band": "medium",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "page": 5,
      "image": "books/T4-NF-01/images/T4-NF-01_P5.png",
      "text": "Then add water and seasoning. Let it boil. Taste it and adjust the seasoning.",
      "layout": "image_top_text_bottom",
      "text_band": "short",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "page": 6,
      "image": "books/T4-NF-01/images/T4-NF-01_P6.png",
      "text": "Now wash the rice and add it to the pot. Put the lid on. Lower the heat and leave it.",
      "layout": "image_top_text_bottom",
      "text_band": "medium",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "page": 7,
      "image": "books/T4-NF-01/images/T4-NF-01_P7.png",
      "text": "When the rice is tender and all the water has been absorbed, the jollof is ready. The bottom of the pot will be slightly browned — this is the best part.",
      "layout": "image_top_text_bottom",
      "text_band": "long",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "page": 8,
      "image": "books/T4-NF-01/images/T4-NF-01_P8.png",
      "text": "Serve the jollof with fried plantain, chicken, or fish. Eat with your family and enjoy.",
      "layout": "image_top_text_bottom",
      "text_band": "short",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
